WEBVTT

00:01.501 --> 00:03.635
You're giving up on the case?

00:03.703 --> 00:05.804
I'm not giving up.
There is no case.

00:05.872 --> 00:08.573
The court rules in favour of
the motion to strike.

00:08.642 --> 00:12.110
The case is dismissed.
<i>My stepdad used to call</i>

00:12.179 --> 00:15.313
David Hanley the Grim Reaper.
My ex is moving.

00:15.316 --> 00:18.950
He's got a job in Winnipeg.
Our marriage was terrible,

00:19.019 --> 00:22.487
but we're great at coparenting.
I can count on him.

00:22.556 --> 00:25.257
All you need to do is sign this.

00:25.325 --> 00:28.160
- A nondisclosure agreement?
<i>- My dad's sins</i>

00:28.228 --> 00:30.662
caught up to him.
That's why we left.

00:30.730 --> 00:32.764
If he finds out
I'm talking to you, I'm dead.

00:32.833 --> 00:35.067
Just give me
something I can use.

00:35.135 --> 00:37.936
<i>Southvale Farms, you gotta
go back. Take a closer look.</i>

00:42.476 --> 00:44.709
- So why are we here?
- We have to find out

00:44.778 --> 00:46.945
exactly what's in the ground
that made Amanda and Steve sick

00:46.947 --> 00:48.947
without attracting
any attention.

00:49.015 --> 00:50.949
And how exactly do we do that?

00:51.017 --> 00:52.951
Ground penetrating radar.

00:53.020 --> 00:55.554
I paid for law school
working summers for Jack's crew.

00:55.622 --> 00:58.657
We'd see the pipe lines before
we even picked up a shovel.

00:58.725 --> 01:02.494
Jack. Thanks for meeting
with us.

01:02.562 --> 01:04.361
You're going
to have to make this quick.

01:04.431 --> 01:06.231
We're already behind
on this job.

01:06.233 --> 01:08.366
- We need a utility scanner.
- We don't think

01:08.435 --> 01:10.368
that the athletic field
is the only place

01:10.437 --> 01:12.904
where Matheson Steel dumped.
You really think

01:12.907 --> 01:15.006
Ben knowingly did this?

01:15.075 --> 01:18.077
We need to find out for sure.
For Georgia.

01:22.282 --> 01:24.983
Hey! Luna, let me get that.

01:25.051 --> 01:26.985
- I got it.
- We don't know

01:27.053 --> 01:29.354
what's in this water.
Well, I wasn't gonna drink it.

01:29.422 --> 01:31.189
Look, this has
been disproportionately

01:31.192 --> 01:34.025
affecting young women. I don't
want you this close to it.

01:34.094 --> 01:36.028
Thank you.

01:42.670 --> 01:44.803
Damn it.

01:44.872 --> 01:46.872
Jack, you find anything
over there?

01:46.874 --> 01:50.008
- Nothing yet.
- Where does

01:50.077 --> 01:52.444
this property end, exactly?
20 feet over that hill.

01:52.512 --> 01:54.546
Then you're into the buffer:

01:54.548 --> 01:56.381
The noman's land
between my property

01:56.449 --> 01:58.283
and the neighbour's.
Nobody owns it.

